# Builder.io Fusion — Project Rules

These rules apply to every task. Do not deviate from them.

## Engineering Standards

Every change must meet all of these. Full detail in `AGENTS.md`.

### React & Next.js
- Server Components by default — `"use client"` only for interactivity (event handlers, state, browser APIs)
- Always `next/image` (never `<img>`), `next/link` (never `<a>` for internal links), `next/font` (already configured)
- Every `page.tsx` exports `metadata` or `generateMetadata` with `title` + `description`
- `generateStaticParams` on all `[slug]` routes; `export const revalidate` on all Builder pages

### TypeScript
- No `any` without an inline comment; no `as` assertions without justification
- `import type` for type-only imports; validate external data at boundaries

### Code Quality
- DRY: shared logic → `utils/`, shared types → `types/`, shared UI → `components/`
- KISS: simplest solution that meets the requirement; no speculative abstractions
- Separation of concerns: Server Components fetch, Client Components interact — never mix
- No dead code: no commented-out blocks, unused imports, or stale variables

### SEO
- One `<h1>` per page; logical heading hierarchy; semantic landmark elements
- Descriptive `alt` text on all images; descriptive link text (never "click here")

### Performance
- Prefer Server Components to reduce client JS bundle
- `next/dynamic` with `ssr: false` for heavy client-only libraries
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` on all animations

### Security
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without DOMPurify sanitization — all Builder HTML fields and user content
- No secrets in client code — never expose API keys or tokens to the browser bundle
- Validate and sanitize all external input (URL params, form data, API responses) before use
- No inline `<script>`, `javascript:` hrefs, or `eval()`-style patterns

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- shadcn semantic tokens maintain contrast — never hardcode hex for text
- All interactive elements: visible focus ring (`focus-visible:ring-[3px] focus-visible:ring-ring/50`)
- Icon-only buttons: `aria-label`; images: `alt`; forms: labels via `FormInput`

## After Every Change
Run both before marking a task complete:
```bash
npx tsc --noEmit   # must pass
npm test           # must pass
```

## Dev Server
- Always start the dev server with `npm run dev -- --webpack`
- Never use `next dev` without `--webpack` — Turbopack is incompatible with Builder Dev Tools

## Config & Model Names
- Never hardcode Builder model names as string literals in pages or components
- All model names and the API key live in `config.ts` — always read from there:
  - `config.envs.builderApiKey`
  - `config.models.page`, `config.models.blogArticle`, etc.
- When adding a new model, add its name to `config.ts` first before using it anywhere

## Builder SDK Usage
- Never use `<Content>` directly — always use the wrapper:
  `import { RenderBuilderContent } from "@/components/builder/RenderBuilderContent"`
- Always guard `notFound()` with both editing and preview checks:
  `if (!content && !isEditing() && !isPreviewing()) return notFound()`
- Always guard `subscribeToEditor` with a `builder.preview` URL param check to prevent
  "Model Name Mismatch" errors — see `docs/skills/builder-io.md` for the exact pattern
- For full SDK patterns, route types, and blog model patterns: `docs/skills/builder-io.md`
- For design system components, tokens, and WCAG rules: `docs/skills/design-system.md`

## Security
- Never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` on Builder HTML fields without DOMPurify sanitization

## Imports & Paths
- Always use the `@/` path alias for internal imports — never use relative paths like `../../`
- Import shadcn UI components from `@/components/ui/` — e.g. `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"`
- Import the Text (typography) component from `@/components/ui/text`
- Import the labeled input wrapper from `@/components/ui/form-input`
- Import the Builder carousel wrapper from `@/components/builder/BuilderCarousel` (only for builder-registry.ts)
- There is NO barrel file — import each component from its own file in `components/ui/`

## Testing
- Tests live in `tests/` — mirroring the component structure (`tests/design-system/`, `tests/blog/`, `tests/layout/`)
- Run with `npm test` (headless) or `npm run test:ui` (interactive)
- Two fixture pages serve as test harnesses — do not link them from the app:
  - `app/design-system/page.tsx` — shadcn components (Button, Badge, FormInput, Card, Carousel, Text, Counter)
  - `app/test/blog-components/page.tsx` — blog components with static mock data
- For full conventions, gotchas, and fixture page patterns: `docs/skills/testing.md`
